The paper discusses compressive sensing (CS) and Bayesian inference, which are both topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of belief propagation (BP) decoding is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Signal Processing (cs.SP), which are also relevant to the paper. The paper also mentions the use of a mixture Gaussian model, which falls under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on signal models and sparse matrices makes it relevant to the sub-category of Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI).
